STEPS TO REPRODUCE:
 1. Start firefox debug build with a fresh profile (empty folder to be populated)
   e.g. mkdir /tmp/foo; ./dist/bin/firefox -profile /tmp/foo -no-remote

ACTUAL RESULTS:
This message goes by, amongst the terminal-spew as Firefox starts up:
{
JavaScript strict warning: chrome://browser/content/tabbrowser.xml, line 1095: reference to undefined property params.referrerURI
}

I viewed that chrome:// URI and found the line of code the message points to.

The code is actually at line #1204 in MXR:
https://mxr.mozilla.org/mozilla-central/source/browser/base/content/tabbrowser.xml?mark=1204-1204#1196
{
> 1196           <![CDATA[
> 1197             var aFromExternal;
> 1198             var aRelatedToCurrent;
> 1199             var aSkipAnimation;
> 1200             if (arguments.length == 2 &&
> 1201                 typeof arguments[1] == "object" &&
> 1202                 !(arguments[1] instanceof Ci.nsIURI)) {
> 1203               let params = arguments[1];
> 1204               aReferrerURI          = params.referrerURI;
> 1205               aCharset              = params.charset;
}

CC'ing dao, since HG blame says he added that line of code back in 2009, and hence he might have some idea of what's going on.  (Though it could easily have become broken since then from changes to the "arguments" variable then.)

